This paper involves the use of neural networks for personalized recommendation in the fashion industry, which falls under the umbrella of machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of embeddings and style vectors suggests a potential application of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques. Additionally, the use of recurrent neural networks and the focus on personalized recommendation suggests a potential overlap with artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
